SIMPLE: heavenly
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heavenly
<hw>Heav"en*ly</hw> <pr>(h⟦ecr⟧v"'n*l⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[AS. <ets>heofonic</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to,
resembling, or inhabiting heaven; celestial; not earthly; <as>as,
<ex>heavenly</ex> regions; <ex>heavenly</ex> music.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As is the <qex>heavenly</qex>, such are they also that are
<qex>heavenly</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>1 Cor. xv. 48.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Appropriate to heaven in character or happiness;
perfect; pure; supremely blessed; <as>as, a <ex>heavenly</ex> race; the
<ex>heavenly</ex>, throng.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The love of heaven makes one <qex>heavenly</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir
P. Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heavenly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Heavenly
<hw>Heav"en*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a manner
resembling that of heaven.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧She was <xex>heavenly</xex>
true.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>By the influence or agency of heaven.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Out <qex>heavenly</qex> guided soul shall climb.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heavenly-minded</ent>⟦br⟧
